annotation.TEXT: Yep, this is the part I remember from raocow's playthrough. Oh, and since the game is playing Beloved Tomboyish Daughter here, I don't have to edit that in myself!
Okay, we've got the rising/falling layer 2, with ON/OFF switches to toggle it. And, there's these ice blocks that I've gotta fry. Better not take any hits here!
Oh, she's now shooting snowflakes at me during this attack. But, since they're cape-thwackable, I don't have to move my butt from the turbo-cape-spin key.
Oh, we're at the end of this room. Okay, am I nearly done yet?
Yeah, there was vanilla SMW castle music here, which got claimed on my first upload attempt, so I went back into WMM and replaced enough of it to prevent the claim.
Okay, I think the audio has returned to normal now. Let's pray that there aren't anymore WMM hiccups...
Fortunately, that Lava Lotus was slow to spew out its projectiles.

1. Part of Cirno's magic is kept in the switches. 2. Get 10 coins in this room and have Yoshi eat 20 dolphins. 3. There's an HP system. 4. Hitting the icicles with a cape will turn them into 9-balls. That's the key!
Moon count: 15
Alright, let's try not to get eaten by that evil Boss Bass this time.
And all of a sudden, autoscrolling. Was that triggered by defeating the Chuck? Maybe.
Hey there, Stretch. How's it going?
Okay, this is pretty neat. In addition to the color change, the room is actually only slippery while the switches are OFF and things are ice-colored.
Sweet! There was a MOOOONNN up there! And yeah, I switched back to the normal audio here because I wanted those 1-up sounds to be audible.
WMM hiccups: 1
BGM: VVVVVV - Path Complete
BGM: DKC2 - Run, Rambi! Run!
ARE YOU PUDDING KIDDING ME?!?!
Uh, oh. Vanilla castle music again. Don't panic. This one didn't last long enough to get a claim.
Really, no power ups?
Yep, Windows Movie Maker did that thing again... Believe it or not, this is actually my fourth attempt to upload this video without any issues.
Thanks, ice block, for not taking out those Urchins that I know you're capable of taking out. Was that a sprite slot issue? Also, I can forget about my reserve cape.
Well, that appears to be it for the Easy path! (So, I guess VVVVVV's Path Complete music was fitting there.)
BGM: GundeadliGne - Cosmique Qubey (Arranged)
Also, I should be careful with how I'm doing the frying here, because of the lava.
Aha, I figured these things would shoot lasers, just like in SMB3. Although these lasers aren't nearly as fast.
Whoa, boy. These vertical bullets have changed to aim for me now, just like Daiyousei's did after I hit her a couple times.

Cirno: "You thought you'd beat me so easily, huh? That I'm an idiot? That I'd just die? That was my DUMMY! I'm not gonna let you call me an idiot any longer! YOU'RE the idiots, idiots! Get out of my face! This old moron's gonna make you pay!" Defeat her using five Goombas!
And now, an underwater segment. I'm glad I brought this ice block with me. Man, how long is this level anyway? I haven't even seen the midpoint yet.
Okay, I've eaten 20, but now what? Do I have to slowly wait until I reach the end of this room or something?
Wow, 5 Yoshi coins all in a row. What is this, Brutal Mario? Unfortunately, I can't take Yoshi through this one pipe, so I must leave him behind. Bye, Yoshi!
She deployed an unexpected snowflake at the same time as the Paragoomba that time, and it froze me in just the perfect spot for Mr. Goomba to go "poof" on my butt.
Of course, it wouldn't be a Cirno level without this theme!
Aw, hidden blocks. No shortcut for me.
Hmm... I'm pretty sure I recall there being more to the Cirno fight...
I'm sick of remaking and reuploading this video now, so since this one doesn't have a copyright claim, and this WMM hiccup is kind of funny, I'll stick with this.
Double gulp!
I'm not sure what Cirno was doing down there... but anyway, it looks like the pattern repeats now.
Pfft... So much for my ice block.
Ah, the HP system ended there, returning my power up status to what it previously was.
Oh, this must be the part where I have to eat 20 dolphins.
Stretch can't be cape-thwacked either.
Whoa, careful!
Missed a coin. Don't care.
Oh, this attack is a bit denser now.
Okay, Cirno's doing different things now. I remember those vertical white bullets, which Daiyousei also used.
That added an additional hazard to the floor, but it shouldn't be very hard to avoid. Okay, I'm going to start speeding up the footage during this attack.
Demo count: 14
Can't cape-thwack those bullets, although I swear I saw one of them move 1 pixel to the left when I tried...
Sweet, and it's a straight-up Cape Feather too! (I guess that block is set to act like a green ! block.)
And there's the Goomba that I need to return to sender.
Nice. First try. I could try for a block factory, but I don't want to waste too much time.
Huh, that one shot both a Bullet Bill and a snowflake.
Huh, Cirno didn't do anything while down there that time...
BGM: Touhou 6 - Cirno's Theme - Beloved Tomboyish Daughter
Gah! I hate when I get hit by a projectile like that while I'm cape-thwacking it. It just doesn't seem right to me. Anyway, I still have 2 HP, and this is Goomba #4.
So, next time, there is no choice but to play Nine-Ball Cirno's Castle (Normal), which means there's no need to vote this time!
BGM: Mega Man 2 - Wily Castle 1 and 2 (Okkusenman)
That is a neat effect, where everything turned icy when I hit the P-switch. So, part of Cirno's magic was indeed kept in the switches!
I'm just going to sit on the turbo-cape-spin button until Cirno changes attacks now.
Yeah, the victory and castle destruction tracks got claimed that time. Fortunately, replacing just the castle destruction music was enough to prevent the claim.
Aw, shrinker stripes. But, I still have my reserve cape!
Oh, man. We're at the rapid layer 2 smashing part.
So, Cirno's Castle (Easy) it is! Oh, and don't worry about my status from touching the electric block. I ended the last episode in this power up state anyway.
I fixed that hiccup, and double-checked to see that it was fixed, but I didn't think WMM would then hiccup in another spot.
Oh, geez! I remember this part from raocow's playthrough! RUN, RUN, RUN!!!
Pfft... Well, that's it for Mr. Goomba, but he did serve me well.
Okay, I'm speeding up the footage now, since this takes a while and not much changes until I reach the end of this room.
Umm... Maybe? Well, let me try to clone this block.
Huh? I thought it was slippery... Oh...
Also, there's some bullet cannons... er, I mean, Bill Blasters.
Oh, right. I forgot that Start+Select acts as a level clear in this hack. Well, no matter, since I've already cleared that level anyway. Okay, voting results time!
Uhh... I may have to take a hit here...
Hot Foot can't be cape-thwacked.
At least there was this silver P-switch which actually removes Boss Bass! Also, I'm probably meant to Yoshi jump into that pipe, but I can reach it without Yoshi jumping!
Cool. You can slide-kill Hot Foot. I guess Mario's butt is powerful enough to smother that kind of fire.
Wait, I thought I returned the footage to normal speed here... Oh, no... Not again...
Anyway, that free cape was nice. So, there's a bunch of things to keep in mind here.

And so Cirno's castle was conquered. Cirno: "I went easy on you..." You've now beaten all the Easy stages. Congratulations! Of course, you should go attempt the Normal stages now. And after Normal, there may very well be Hard and Lunatic...
...Well! That just happened... One moment, please...
BGM: Hero Core - Boss Battle
She also tossed a diagonal snowflake at me.
Next, we have cape-thwackable projectiles from below.
...Or not! Wow, I'm surprised I made that!
Fortunately, the sped-up castle theme doesn't get claimed. Also, I decided to leave the second P-switch behind, to hopefully reduce lag in this room. Hopefully I won't need it.
My first two attempts had copyright claims on the vanilla SMW castle music and another SMW track later on, and my third attempt had WMM hiccup in a different place.
FINISH HER!
Oh. Well, so much for that shell, but it did help a little. Will this thing gobble up the Chomp as well?
DOUBLE KILL!
There were two diagonal snowflakes there that time.
I'm going to stay on this ledge up here where Boss Bass can't reach me.
Pfft... Well, I recklessly rushed into that one, and couldn't turn around in time due to the slippery floor. I hope I don't need to burn anything more...
Oh, what do we have here? Fairies? Hmm... It seems that I can't harm them in any way. I bet they're just resprited Eeries.
And fortunately, I didn't have to replace any more of the SMW castle music to prevent a claim, likely because of this P-switch here. Push!
Yep! Okay, please tell me I'm near the end now.
Hi, Yoshi! ...Oh, yeah. I did notice that there wasn't a "no Yoshi" intro to this level.
Whoa, geez! How did I manage to jump at just the right time to dodge that?!
Huh. Somehow I destroyed it with this Goomba without the Goomba dying. How does that even work? Well, I'm not complaining, since I can clone up another feather now!
Well, hello there, Hot Foot...
And of course, let's make sure to eat at least 20 dolphins. Interestingly, my coins just so happen to be at exactly 0 now, so it'll be easy to see how many I've eaten this time.
Zap! Yeah, I simply take normal damage, just like with spikes and munchers.
Aw, the game shrunk me anyway. It must really want me to be small now. Anyway, there's the midpoint, finally.
Okay, so Cirno's throwing snowballs at me, and always matches my height if I jump. However, these are just like Pitching Chuck's baseballs, and can be cape-thwacked.
Yeah, there was vanilla SMW boss music here. Anyway, here's Cirno, and the 3-HP system is in effect again, which also makes me caped this time.
Awesome. Now, this part should be simple. Just hit ON/OFF switches as needed to keep the spike ceiling from dropping very much.
Too bad the snowflakes are apparently immune to thrown weapons.
DOUBLE KILL!
Yeah, can't cape-thwack those things. I think I tried that before in an earlier level, actually.
Whoa! That was close! Okay, she actually did something while down there that time!
There we go! This very slow-paced fight is done now!
Okay, here's Goomba #2, right back at ya!
I wonder why those Bill Blasters are a different color...
Now, remember how I said earlier that on my second attempt to upload this video, a later SMW track had gotten a copyright claim?
BGM: Sora - Tsih's Theme.
Whoa, careful. Try not to grab the lowest ice blocks.
Also, more layer 2 shenanigans, with the smashing effect this time.
Delicious!
Well, I won't literally sit on it. Do you have any idea how tricky it would be to position my butt so that it's pressing just a single particular key on the keyboard?
Anyway, this one's pretty easy. Cape-thwack the falling icicles to turn them into ⑨s, and then toss them back at Cirno.
Those stripes removed my cape. Also, I wonder why that Chomp is leaving some blocks behind...
Hey, Koopa. Let me use your shell, please.
Meh. Whatever.
Ooh, this music! As long as it's not overused, it's awesome!
Before I enter this pipe, is there anything above the screen here?
Whoa, munchers.
Hello, and welcome back to Scarlet Devil Mario! Now, people wanted to see me touch an electric block, so here you go.
They fire the same things as the other ones.
Anyway, the HP system is present in this room, and I already took one dumb muncher hit back there.
Nice. That's Goomba #3.
Whoa. Fortunately, getting knocked off Yoshi doesn't cost me HP (unlike in Toadette Strikes).
Oh, hold on. I want to try cloning an ON/OFF switch here.
To be continued... Ze!
